{"sectionId":493,"sectionIdLiteral":"493","humanId":"lesson-89","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"ownlineNumber":"Lesson 89"},"annotation":"W-89","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text review-lesson review-2 lesson-89\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"493#0\"><p class=\"p-review-intro\"><span data-sentence-id=\"493#0:1\">These are our review ideas for today:</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"493#1\"><p class=\"p-lesson-ref\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>(<span class=\"lref\">77</span>) <b>I am entitled to miracles.</b></span></p> <p class=\"p-normal\"><span data-sentence-id=\"493#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>I am entitled to miracles because I am under no laws but God‚Äôs.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>His laws release me from all grievances, and replace them with miracles.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>And I would accept the miracles in place of the grievances, which are but illusions that hide the miracles beyond.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>Now I would accept only what the laws of God entitle me to have, that I may use it on behalf of the function He has given me.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"493#2\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>You might use these suggestions for specific applications of this idea:</span></p> <p class=\"p-prayer\"><span data-sentence-id=\"493#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Behind this is a miracle to which I am entitled.<br/></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Let me not hold a grievance against you, [name], but offer you the miracle that belongs to you instead.<br/></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Seen truly, this offers me a miracle.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"493#3\"><p class=\"p-lesson-ref\"><span class=\"pnr\">3.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#3:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>(<span class=\"lref\">78</span>) <b>Let miracles replace all grievances.</b></span></p> <p class=\"p-normal\"><span data-sentence-id=\"493#3:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>By this idea do I unite my will with the Holy Spirit‚Äôs, and perceive them as one.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#3:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>By this idea do I accept my release from hell.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#3:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>By this idea do I express my willingness to have all my illusions be replaced with truth, according to God‚Äôs plan for my salvation.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#3:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>I would make no exceptions and no substitutes.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#3:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>I want all of Heaven and only Heaven, as God wills me to have.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"493#4\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">4.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#4:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Useful specific forms for applying this idea would be:</span></p> <p class=\"p-prayer\"><span data-sentence-id=\"493#4:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>I would not hold this grievance apart from my salvation.<br/></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#4:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Let our grievances be replaced by miracles, [name].<br/></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"493#4:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Beyond this is the miracle by which all my grievances are replaced.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"These are our review ideas for today: (77) I am entitled to miracles. I am entitled to miracles because I am under no laws but God‚Äôs. His laws release me from all grievances, and replace them with","contentType":"acim-content","seoTitle":"Lesson 89: Review (77 and 78) | ACIM","seoDescription":"‚ú® A Course in Miracles with üéß Audio! Read and listen to Lesson¬†89 ‚ÄúReview (77 and 78)‚Äù: These are our review ideas for today: (77) I am entitled to miracles. I am entitled to miracles‚Ä¶","desktopBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part I","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":403,"slugs":["lesson-1","nothing-i-see-means-anything"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Review II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":484,"slugs":["review-ii","introduction"]}},{"label":"Lesson 89","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":493,"slugs":["review-ii","lesson-89"]}}],"mobileBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part I","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":403,"slugs":["lesson-1","nothing-i-see-means-anything"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Review II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":484,"slugs":["review-ii","introduction"]}},{"label":"Lesson 89","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":493,"slugs":["review-ii","lesson-89"]}}],"seoBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"A Course in Miracles","leadsTo":"dashboard"},{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part I","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":403,"slugs":["lesson-1","nothing-i-see-means-anything"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Review II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":484,"slugs":["review-ii","introduction"]}},{"label":"Lesson 89","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":493,"slugs":["review-ii","lesson-89"]}}],"slugs":["review-ii","lesson-89"],"canonicalLink":"https://acim.org/acim/review-ii/lesson-89/en/s/493","link":"https://acim.org/acim/review-ii/lesson-89/en/s/493","shortLink":"https://acim.org/acim/en/s/493","previousSectionId":492,"previousSectionSlugs":["review-ii","lesson-88"],"previousSectionLink":"https://acim.org/acim/review-ii/lesson-88/en/s/492","nextSectionId":494,"nextSe